21/05/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The largest ethnic Albanian party in Macedonia, the Democratic Union for Integration, is reportedly negotiating a merger with a smaller party, the National Democratic Party. Citing reliable party sources, <I>Dnevnik</I> reported Tuesday (20 May) that talks are close to completion; the final issues are composition of the new joint leadership and reallocations of some inter-party functions. (Dnevnik - 20/05/03)
